06/10/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis met with Russian counterpart Mikhail Fradkov on Thursday (October 5th) about energy issues, particularly the possibility of renewing an agreement with Russia for the supply of natural gas after 2016. 
They also reaffirmed their commitment to the Burgas-Alexandroupolis oil pipeline involving Greece, Russia and Bulgaria. 
Within the framework of the visit, they endorsed an agreement on co-operation in tourism and on the settlement of the Russian Federation's outstanding debts to Greece. 
(ANA-MPA - 05/10/06)
